<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="27" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1951,2012]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,151,1688]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="27" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1951,1976]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Style with apical third moderately curved ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[869,972,1952,1976]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
Figs 
<number box="[926,972,1952,1976]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7–8</number>
</figureCitation>
); connective Y-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1242,1310,1952,1976]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
Fig. 
<number box="[1295,1310,1952,1976]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
); aedeagus without dorsal apodeme, curved, S-shaped, shaft with apical fifth abruptly curved ventrally, one pair of spiniform dorsal preapical processes forming “V” in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[796,915,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Figs 
<number box="[855,915,151,175]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="9.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="9.0">9–10</number>
</figureCitation>
); anal tube with pair of moderately elongated basiventral processes, apices slightly curved and sclerotized, reaching posteroventral margin of pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[1325,1393,188,212]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Fig. 
<number box="[1377,1393,188,212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
