<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="27" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1688]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,454,223,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Measurements (mm).</emphasis>
Male 
<typeStatus box="[531,634,223,247]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">holotype</typeStatus>
: total length 7.06; crown median length 0.79; transocular width 1.49; interocular width 0.80; frons basal width 0.77; frons length 1.01; pronotum median length 0.67; width between humeri 1.68; mesonotum median length 1.07; mesonotum maximum width 1.32; forewing length 5.61; forewing maximum width 1.49.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1688]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,367,367,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">General color.</emphasis>
Body pale yellow with orange maculae (
<figureCitation box="[833,963,367,391]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 13" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1984,2007]" captionTargetBox="[180,1392,310,1948]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[180,1393,165,1948]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 13. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 11, dorsal view; 12, lateral view; 13, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279026/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Figs 
<number box="[891,963,367,391]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="12.0" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="11.0">11–13</number>
</figureCitation>
). Crown yellow, with two pairs of orange maculae, one subtriangular and close to anterior margin, other, subquadrangular and close to posterior margin, adjacent to compound eyes (
<figureCitation box="[487,556,439,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Fig. 
<number box="[543,556,439,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
); ocelli yellow (
<figureCitation box="[753,859,439,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Figs 
<number box="[814,859,439,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
</figureCitation>
); gena and lorum pale yellow; frons and clypeus orange (
<figureCitation box="[243,346,476,500]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Figs 
<number box="[300,346,476,500]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pronotum with lateral margins pale yellow, central and mid-lateral region, orange. Mesonotum whitish with two ferruginous lateral subtriangular stains, and a central ferruginous longitudinal stripe, narrowed at base and enlarged at apical half (
<figureCitation box="[524,590,548,572]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Fig. 
<number box="[577,590,548,572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Forewings and hindwings semi-hyaline, yellowish, with yellow venation (
<figureCitation box="[159,229,583,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,229,583,607]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Mesothoracic pleura pale yellow. Legs orange, tibiae and tarsi distal portion greenish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1688]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,343,619,644]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Description.</emphasis>
External morphological characters as in generic description, except: forewings about 3.5 times longer than its maximum width; venation weakly visible (
<figureCitation box="[797,867,655,679]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Fig. 
<number box="[850,867,655,679]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[887,943,655,679]" name="India" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Hind</collectingCountry>
leg femoral formula 
<number box="[1181,1197,655,679]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[1214,1230,655,679]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[1247,1257,655,679]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="1.0">1</number>
. Male genitalia. Pygofer, in lateral view, enlarged basally, apical half slightly narrowed towards rounded apex; with macrosetae on middle portion of ventral margin and apex (
<figureCitation box="[648,717,727,751]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Fig. 
<number box="[701,717,727,751]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plates enlarged at basal two-thirds, lateral margins with preapical constriction, narrowed at apical third; separated only in apical quarter; dorsal surface with grouped setae on median portion and ventral surface with sparse setae at apex (
<figureCitation box="[944,1013,799,823]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Fig. 
<number box="[997,1013,799,823]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Style without preapical lobe; lateral margins smooth; apex truncated and sclerotized, moderatly curved ventrally; with a pair of setae on ventral preapical portion (
<figureCitation box="[288,398,871,896]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Figs. 
<number box="[353,398,871,896]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="7.8">7, 8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Connective Y-shaped; about half length of style (
<figureCitation box="[975,1044,871,895]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Fig. 
<number box="[1028,1044,871,895]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus with robust preatrium, corresponding to one third of total length of aedeagus, articulated to connective (
<figureCitation box="[1057,1126,908,932]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Fig. 
<number box="[1110,1126,908,932]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
); in lateral view, curved, Sshaped, shaft with apical fifth abruptly curved ventrally, apex slender and pointed; dorsal apodeme absent; one pair of spiniform dorsal preapical processes forming “V” in ventral view; gonopore apical (
<figureCitation box="[1115,1236,980,1004]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Figs. 
<number box="[1177,1236,980,1004]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="9.1">9, 10</number>
</figureCitation>
). Anal tube membranous, with pair of moderately elongated basiventral processes, with apices slightly curved and sclerotized, reaching posteroventral margin of pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[640,708,1052,1076]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Fig. 
<number box="[692,708,1052,1076]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
